 -" title="Supporting autistic individuals Mental health challenges and solutions in Birmingham - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-243_ pf-image-1"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-e308" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-uojGG hMqLeX pf-244_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:800px" class="sc-ilfuhL bpQaoh"><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-245_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-246_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-247_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practice</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-377_ pf-heading-1-h3">Legislation such as the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) and the Individuals with Disabilities Education Act (IDEA) provide legal protections and rights for individuals with autism, including access to appropriate mental health services and accommodations. Best practices for supporting mental health in autism include early intervention, person-centred care, and collaboration with other healthcare providers and support services.</h3></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-b05b" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-uojGG hMqLeX pf-252_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1000px" class="sc-ilfuhL bpQaoh"><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-253_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-254_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Healthcare_professionals_training_Navigating_autism_and_mental_health_in_autism_evaluation_in_Manchester_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1716373557" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Healthcare_professionals_training_Navigating_autism_and_mental_hea